interactions.flavorLineOne: Once you have proven yourself worthy of the prophecy, bring it to the Infinite Forge.
Brother Vance holds out his hands and accepts the gift. It's hard to tell his expression beneath that blindfold and hood, but you catch a hint of a smile.

Brother Vance gestures for you to hold out your hand, and carefully deposits a handful of small, smooth candies into your palm.

"You call this celebration of yours 'Festival of the Lost,'" he says. "But remember, Guardian, that the dead are not truly lost. They are simply inaccessible to us." He pauses, then adds offhandedly, "For the most part."

"Osiris would be proud to call you his kin, Guardian. Your Light's glow is like a beacon, as is this Lighthouse, to all who would stand against Darkness."

Mercury has many challenges to face. Continue to explore and complete the various activities here, and Brother Vance will reward you.

Panoptes is gone, but much of the Forest is still under Vex control.

The Infinite Forest is well, suffice to say, infinite. There are many more mysteries still to discover among its uncountable branches.

"You are welcome here, Guardian. The tales of your deedsboth in the past and those yet to comehint at a legend in the making."

Brother Vance offers bounties, quests, and various rewards for Guardians who complete activities on Mercury.

Challenge yourself with adventures, patrols, public events, and a Lost Sector to earn Brother Vance's adulation.

Brother Vance takes the stalk of celery from you and weighs it in his hand. "I will have to mm, meditate on this gift, I suppose."

He turns back to his opened book, brushing his fingers over the pages. "The Forest is strange to me at this time of year. The wiser I am, the more Osiris's plans seem to evade me. I suppose that is the way."
